title: Wielichówko
content:
Wielichówko [vjɛliˈxufkɔ] (German: Münsterberg) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kobylanka, within Stargard County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland.[1] It lies approximately 6 kilometres (4 mi) north of Kobylanka, 13 km (8 mi) north-west of Stargard, and 21 km (13 mi) east of the regional capital Szczecin.

For the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.

The village has a population of 60.
